reviews_data.review_text:
Best coffee shop in Charlotte for remote work!

I have been exploring different coffee shops around Charlotte to work for a few hours on weekdays as a way to get out of the house since I work from home full time (Mortgage Broker)

So far I have tried the top 10 or so places & this is my favorite. The music is spot on for my taste, have heard them play some of my favorite artists that are not very well known.

If you like Beach House, Mac Demarco, Lana Del Rey, Castlebeat, Cigarettes After Sex & Lorde - you will love this place

The vibe is industrial (mostly black) with some fresh plants for a pop of color.

Plenty of seating and lots of wall plugs for charging.

There is a massive uncovered parking lot just a block over that has no time limit & is free.

Highly recommend checking out HEX!
Great cortado
Great experience. Don’t change or lose the quality

Ordered the Avacado Tartine and an iced vanilla latte.
Pretty good!
Set outside with the sounds of a light rain and the birds. Very peaceful and relaxing environment.

Had some time to kill and decided to check out Camp North End since I was in the area. I am still very new to the area and hadn't yet heard of HEX, but when I saw it I knew I had to stop in and check it out.

The way the entire building (and most of Camp North End for that matter) is wrapped in vines and obscured by a multitude of different thriving plants really appealed to me. The inside of this place was just as cool, with a minimalistic and somewhat dark industrial aesthetic. Contrary to many specialty coffee shops, HEX had an abundance of indoor and outdoor seating, which I appreciated.

All of the staff members were extremely friendly, and although it was pretty busy, my coffee came out relatively quickly. I was also pleasantly surprised to find a lot of their roasts were extremely fresh, and at the time I was here, all the beans on the shelf were roasted three days prior. I got their seasonal latte iced with whole milk and it was everything I would expect from a specialty roaster. I didn't try any of the pastries, but will definitely be returning in order to do so.

Although this was my first time trying HEX, I immediately knew this would not be my last. If you're looking for amazing beans, delicious coffee/matcha, or a place to just get away for a bit, I would highly recommend stopping by and giving them a try.
Matcha, coffee and breakfasts are delicious 🤌🏼
Hands down the best coffee in Charlotte.
One of my favorite coffee shops in Charlotte
Great service, delicious espresso drink.

We’ve frequented Hex since their pop up days. Consistently the best coffee in Charlotte and I’d say most major cities. It’s always our favorite. We use their beans at home— just so dang good and reliable. We’ve tried other premium roasters but we keep coming back. The new cafe is awesome. The taro yogurt and hex special are top notch. I only wish they would sell the vanilla syrup by the bottle bc it’s the BEST. Thanks guys and gals!

This was our first visit at Hex on a Saturday afternoon located at Camp North End in Charlotte, NC.  The atmosphere was inviting, the staff were friendly, and the food was delicious.  Our friends ordered items seen in the attached photos. While it’s a small coffee shop, it’s also a great place to bring your laptop and eat while you work.  Enjoy!

My visit to HEX camp north end was memorable for all the wrong reasons. I shelled out for an expensive coffee, only to discover they were remarkably bland – truly, the cheapest supermarket fare surpasses their "offerings." The real surprise came when I was informed that using my laptop was almost a "criminal offense" in this establishment, a rule they apparently keep secret until after you've ordered. There were no signs anywhere indicating this policy. Given that the café was completely deserted, I can only assume their business model involves extracting payment before revealing their laptop hostility and showing customers the door.
The empty café speaks volumes about their customer treatment.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Julia, 

I am extremely sorry about how you felt yesterday. We launched our dinner service this week and were trying to flip our space to be more food centric. The laptop policy was a miscommunication from our team. If you don't mind emailing hexcoffee@gmail.com I would like to try and make this right for you. Once again we apologize.

reviews_data.review_text: Me and my friends love this place! It’s one of our favorite spots to get work done—we can sit there for hours and feel super comfortable. The drinks are great, especially their matcha lattes, which are my go-to. The food is good too, a little greasy at times, and a lot of the menu includes pork, but I really enjoyed their other options like the waffles. Definitely a chill spot with a great vibe!

Hex Coffee is an absolute gem. The coffee itself was excellent — the espresso was smooth and well-balanced, and the filter brew was also very good. But what really made the experience stand out was the barista. She was incredibly friendly and welcoming, and when I asked for recommendations on other coffee spots in Charlotte, she gave me honest and thoughtful suggestions, which I really appreciated.

The atmosphere is relaxed yet vibrant, and as a bonus, I finally got to try Liquid Death water — love the concept of ditching plastic in favor of canned water. It’s clever, impactful, and surprisingly refreshing.

Overall, Hex Coffee delivers both in quality and hospitality. Highly, highly recommend this place to anyone visiting or living in Charlotte.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey thank you so much for coming in truly means a ton!

The barista was working completely by herself, and you’d never know it — she was fast, super friendly, and kept the energy positive the whole time. I ordered an iced oatmeal mocha, and it was absolutely delicious — perfectly balanced, not too sweet, and exactly what I needed. It's rare to see someone handle a rush solo with that much grace and skill. Big props to her and to Hex for delivering such a great experience. I'll definitely be back!

Ordering was easy, and they bring your drink to you once you’ve found a spot. There’s **plenty of seating both indoors and outside**, which is a huge plus. It can get a little noisy if folks nearby are chatting, so I’d recommend bringing headphones if you’re there to focus.

I ordered a **latte with almond milk**, and it was spot-on. Smooth, flavorful, and just what I needed. I’ll definitely be back—this is a solid spot to sip, work, or just vibe.

Best coffee shop in Charlotte for remote work!

I have been exploring different coffee shops around Charlotte to work for a few hours on weekdays as a way to get out of the house since I work from home full time (Mortgage Broker)

So far I have tried the top 10 or so places & this is my favorite. The music is spot on for my taste, have heard them play some of my favorite artists that are not very well known.

If you like Beach House, Mac Demarco, Lana Del Rey, Castlebeat, Cigarettes After Sex & Lorde - you will love this place

The vibe is industrial (mostly black) with some fresh plants for a pop of color.

Had some time to kill and decided to check out Camp North End since I was in the area. I am still very new to the area and hadn't yet heard of HEX, but when I saw it I knew I had to stop in and check it out.

The way the entire building (and most of Camp North End for that matter) is wrapped in vines and obscured by a multitude of different thriving plants really appealed to me. The inside of this place was just as cool, with a minimalistic and somewhat dark industrial aesthetic. Contrary to many specialty coffee shops, HEX had an abundance of indoor and outdoor seating, which I appreciated.

All of the staff members were extremely friendly, and although it was pretty busy, my coffee came out relatively quickly. I was also pleasantly surprised to find a lot of their roasts were extremely fresh, and at the time I was here, all the beans on the shelf were roasted three days prior. I got their seasonal latte iced with whole milk and it was everything I would expect from a specialty roaster. I didn't try any of the pastries, but will definitely be returning in order to do so.

Although this was my first time trying HEX, I immediately knew this would not be my last. If you're looking for amazing beans, delicious coffee/matcha, or a place to just get away for a bit, I would highly recommend stopping by and giving them a try.
